ack grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky."},{"version":"black","text":"It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger."},{"version":"white","text":"It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger."},{"version":"black-2","text":"It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger."},{"version":"white-2","text":"It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger."},{"version":"x","text":"When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder."},{"version":"y","text":"The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this\u2014the Pok\u00e9mon uses the light of the stars as its energy."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this\u2014the Pok\u00e9mon uses the light of the stars as its energy."},{"version":"sun","text":"While it\u2019s believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pok\u00e9mon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep."},{"version":"moon","text":"In battle, it throws punches with all four arms. The power of each individual blow is piddly, so it aims to win by quantity rather than quality."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"It\u2019s said that the patterns on its back are related to the stars in the night sky, but the details of that relationship remain unclear."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you